00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:59,400
- Yes, I mean we'll work weekends.
- Weekends are very good for me.

248
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,800
Weekends. Good idea.

249
00:16:02,100 --> 00:16:04,900
Give us plenty of time together,
no distractions.

250
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,500
It is Labor Day.

251
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,500
I got an idea.

252
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:17,500
How would you two like to come
to my house at the beach?

253
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:20,700
- Me?
- Us?

254
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:22,300
Yeah. Hampton Island.

255
00:16:22,300 --> 00:16:25,000
Ever been there? Well, you will love it.

256
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:27,200
When we're not working,
there are distractions.

257
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:30,000
There are women, swimming,
boating, famous people.

258
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:34,400
Well?

259
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:35,400
- Love to!
- Okay.

260
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,300
Good! It's settled.

261
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:40,800
We are going to have a good time,
I guarantee.

262
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:42,600
My secretary will write down
the directions...

263
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:45,000
- give you the ferry schedule.
- The ferry schedule?

264
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:48,300
It's the only way to get there,
unless you have a boat. I don't know.

265
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:49,900
I have never even been on a boat.

266
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:52,300
I was once on the Staten Island Ferry
with my folks...

267
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:56,100
Whatever. You come out Friday night,
you'll have a great time, I guarantee it.

268
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:59,000
I'll even drive you back to the city myself
on Monday. Okay?

269
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:01,100
We don't know what to say, Bernie.

270
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:03,800
You don't have to say anything.

271
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,900
If you two uncovered what I think
you uncovered...

272
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:10,400
old Bernie here owes you both a great deal.
I mean it sincerely.

273
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,600
Now get out of here. Go on.

274
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:18,700
He loves us.

275
00:17:18,900 --> 00:17:22,900
The man absolutely loves us.

276
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:26,300
You have to kill them, Vito.

277
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:39,500
Let me explain something to you.

278
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:43,900
We don't do that anymore.
We are a corporation now.

279
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:47,100
We are in the market. We invest.

280
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:50,800
Real estate. Car rentals. Parking lots.

281
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,300
Parking lots. That's good.

282
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:57,800
- I understand that, but...
- Didn't I order the walnut dressing?

283
00:17:57,700 --> 00:18:00,100
- Yes, you did.
- Taste that.

284
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:04,600
Does that taste
anything like walnut dressing? Tell me.

285
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:07,500
This is the raspberry vinaigrette.

286
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:10,900
Should I have Paulie go
and talk to the chef?

287
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:16,800
This goddamn raspberry vinaigrette...

288
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,200
Excuse me, Vito.

289
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:32,900
I know how important food is to you,
I mean...

290
00:18:34,100 --> 00:18:36,000
But we've got a problem here.

291
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:39,200
I give problems. I don't get problems.

292
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:46,600
How do you propose to handle it?

293
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:52,500
Let's make it a murder-suicide job. All right?

294
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,400
Okay, gentlemen?

295
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:58,100
I'll plant some money, fake a note,
and they can take the rap and...

296
00:18:58,100 --> 00:19:00,900
I won't even have to change the books.

297
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,700
What do you think?

298
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:10,800
I like it. It's creative.

299
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:17,100
I am a little rusty. But it'll come back to me.

300
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:23,900
Okay.

301
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:29,100
- Do it.
- This is good.

302
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:31,700
I mean this is really good. Good.

303
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:37,100
I think we are going to have some fun.

304
00:19:41,300 --> 00:19:44,600
- I have to get going. I really do.
- What, no dessert?

305
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:48,000
They do a wonderful crème brûlée here.
It's delicious.

306
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:51,700
No, gentlemen, I really must be going.
Thanks for dinner, Vito.

307
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,100
I got to go powder my nose.

308
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,300
Forget the accident with the two guys.

309
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:19,700
Take care of Lomax.

310
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:22,600
He's getting too careless...

311
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:25,200
too greedy.

312
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:29,500
Besides...

313
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:32,700
he's screwing my girlfriend.

314
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:38,600
But you said we were going to
spend the weekend at the beach!

315
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:41,500
You heard the conversation.
What am I supposed to do about it?

316
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:42,400
- Bernie.
- What?

317
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:46,000
I told Vito I was going to spend
some time with my mother!

318
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,300
I have to see you, Bernie.

319
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,600
Cut it out.

320
00:20:57,100 --> 00:21:00,000
- What's wrong with you? Wait a minute.
- What?

321
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,900
- I have an idea.
- What?

322
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:04,800
You are on, 9:00 Friday night.
I'll be at the apartment.

323
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:06,700
Just use your key. All right?

324
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:09,600
I'll wear something special.

325
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:12,700
I bet you never had sweet and sour
matzo balls before.

326
00:21:12,700 --> 00:21:13,700
No.

327
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:19,300
- I am glad you finally asked me out.
- You are?

328
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:22,600
I wish you had asked me out sooner.

329
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:26,000
Today was my last day at work.
I am going back to college.

330
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:29,000
We could still have
this weekend together, right?

331
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,000
I am spending it with my folks.

332
00:21:30,900 --> 00:21:33,400
- Are your folks in town?
- No.

333
00:21:36,900 --> 00:21:40,500
Is this the intimate evening
I promised you, or what?

334
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,900
You think there's anywhere we could go
to just sit and talk...

335
00:21:43,900 --> 00:21:47,200
and not have to scream
and get run over by garbage trucks?

336
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:49,100
- Hey, want to throw her in?
- How you doing?

337
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:52,200
I'd invite you to my apartment,
but I have five roommates.

338
00:21:52,100 --> 00:21:54,400
And they are all at home
doing their hair right now.

339
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:58,400
That's a lot of hair. But it's clean. I like that.

340
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:02,800
It's either that or living with my parents,
and I don't think that's a good idea.

341
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:06,100
I can't blame you. Who'd want
to live with their folks? That's no good.

342
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:09,100
- Do you have any roommates?
- No. Roommates? No. None.

343
00:22:09,300 --> 00:22:10,800
Why don't we go to your place?

344
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:14,400
Come on, baby. You're not a woman.
Are you? Tell me the truth.

345
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:21,100
Okay.

346
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:37,400
Why are you tiptoeing?

347
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:40,000
Because...

348
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:46,900
the people who live downstairs,
they're very light sleepers.

349
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:50,300
They get angry when I walk.

350
00:22:51,300 --> 00:22:53,200
Why are you whispering?

351
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:56,300
- Am I?
- Yes.

352
00:22:56,700 --> 00:23:01,100
I am. That's because of the walls.
They are too thin.

353
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:05,500
- Make yourself at home.
- Thank you.

354
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:21,400
Look at this teak.
I mean this whole apartment.

355
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:23,900
Sort of '60s style.

356
00:23:23,900 --> 00:23:26,900
Yeah. I know.
I've been meaning to redo that for years.

357
00:23:26,900 --> 00:23:30,000
No, I love it. I mean, it's very hip.

358
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:33,400
I think you have done the place beautifully.

359
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:35,600
I like it. It's home.

360
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:38,500
You know, it's a side of you
I never would have expected.

361
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:40,100
I'm very impressed.

362
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:41,700
- Are you?
- Yeah.

363
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:44,100
About what?

364
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:47,200
This apartment has got to be expensive.

365
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:51,500
So obviously you could have taken me
to some flash restaurant instead of that...

366
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:54,900
Is "dump" the word you are groping for?

367
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:57,400
You didn't like Hymie's Hunan?

368
00:23:57,800 --> 00:24:01,000
- It's a four-star dive.
- It was great. I loved it.

369
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:04,200
It's just that some men
would try to impress women by...

370
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:06,300
pretending to be something they are not.

371
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:09,800
I absolutely agree. That's a terrible way
to begin a relationship.

372
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:12,500
Pretending to be something you are not.

373
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:13,700
Oh, God.

374
00:24:13,900 --> 00:24:16,900
You don't have to answer this
if you don't want to...

375
00:24:16,900 --> 00:24:19,600
but how do you afford a place like this?

376
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:23,800
I don't like to brag.

377
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:27,000
I just feel uncomfortable
showing off my money...

378
00:24:26,900 --> 00:24:31,000
but I've made some wise investments.
I dabble in the stock market.

379
00:24:31,100 --> 00:24:35,200
And of course my parents
were rather well off.

380
00:24:35,700 --> 00:24:37,500
Do you want to sit?

381
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:42,000
They passed away?

382
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:43,900
Yes.

383
00:24:44,100 --> 00:24:46,100
They must have been young.

384
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:48,100
Oh, yeah.

385
00:24:50,700 --> 00:24:53,300
I feel I can trust you.

386
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:57,300
They were in a train accident.

387
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:59,900
Yeah, I mean I don't know
what it was with trains...

388
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:03,400
but they just always liked to travel in trains.

389
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:05,600
I am sorry.

390
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:08,700
- How awful for you.
- Yeah.

391
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:15,200
You know, I always thought trains
were so much safer than planes.

392
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:18,800
Well, actually, a plane...

393
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:21,600
fell on the train.

394
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:47,800
- Richard.
- Gwen.

395
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:54,000
There's a man in his underwear
in your kitchen.

396
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:56,700
He's... He's with me.

397
00:25:59,500 --> 00:26:01,800
He's my butler. But...

398
00:26:02,300 --> 00:26:04,900
- You have a butler?
- Yeah. Don't get him started.

399
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:08,100
He'll just go away if you just be quiet.

400
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:21,600
Sorry. I didn't realize you had company.

401
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:23,300
Good evening, young lady.

402
00:26:23,300 --> 00:26:25,400
That's all right, Monroe.

403
00:26:27,900 --> 00:26:32,500
Yes, will you, please, just go lay out
my navy blue suit for the morning?

404
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:33,400
Please.

405
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:35,800
- How about if I lay you out?
- Very well.

406
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:43,800
- You let your butler talk to you like that?
- Well, he is a vet.

407
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:46,100
He has got a steel plate in his head.

408
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:50,100
Gwen, it's not what you think.

409
00:26:50,500 --> 00:26:52,200
Goodbye, Richard.

410
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:19,200
I'll grab the bow line.

411
00:27:19,300 --> 00:27:22,400
- Hey, Skeet. How are you doing?
- Hey, Mr. Lomax.

412
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:25,100
Here you go, my friend.
Buy yourself a girlfriend.

413
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,700
Where have you been, Candy?

414
00:27:31,600 --> 00:27:34,600
- Hey, Bernie. How about a drink?
- A little bit later.

415
00:27:37,600 --> 00:27:40,900
- Yo, Bernie. The cocktail flag is up.
- A little bit later.

416
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:43,500
Booze and women.
That is my lifestyle and I love it!

417
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:44,800
And I!

418
00:28:19,900 --> 00:28:22,700
- George, how are you?
- Nice to see you, Mr. Lomax.

419
00:28:25,700 --> 00:28:27,900
What are you doing here?
I fired you last week.

420
00:28:27,900 --> 00:28:29,400
- I just want my $90, okay?
- Bullshit!

421
00:28:29,500 --> 00:28:31,900
You drank my liquor
and the toilets still don't work.

422
00:28:31,900 --> 00:28:33,700
I don't want to see you.

423
00:28:33,900 --> 00:28:35,200
Get out of here!

424
00:28:35,800 --> 00:28:38,200
You come back again,
I am going to call the cops!

425
00:28:38,100 --> 00:28:39,900
You son of a bitch.

426
00:28:45,500 --> 00:28:49,400
- I am sorry. I think she needs a little B-12.
- Whatever.

427
00:28:49,300 --> 00:28:52,100
<i>This is Bernie. Leave a message,
I'll get right back to you.</i>

428
00:28:52,100 --> 00:28:54,100
- Goodbye, Mr. Lomax.
- Bye.

429
00:28:54,100 --> 00:28:55,600
Hello?

430
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:59,300
Hey, Lomax. It's Paulie.
I just got to the island.

431
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:00,600
You are early.

432
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:03,000
Those schmucks are not coming
until the 6:00 ferry...

433
00:29:02,900 --> 00:29:05,400
- and I still have to plant the note.
- Yeah.

434
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:06,700
So where is your house?

435
00:29:06,800 --> 00:29:08,800
It's on the point, top of the dune.

436
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:11,600
Look, Paulie,
don't kill them while I am around.

437
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:13,700
Bernie, we are on a phone here.

438
00:29:13,700 --> 00:29:15,500
Right. You are right. Okay, I am sorry.

439
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:18,700
The point is, I just want to be
back in New York with an alibi, okay?

440
00:29:18,700 --> 00:29:20,700
Yeah. Don't worry about it.

441
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:32,700
Oh, God!

442
00:29:34,500 --> 00:29:36,100
Rich. It is leaving. Come on!

443
00:29:36,100 --> 00:29:38,500
I told you we should've taken
a taxi from the station.

444
00:29:38,500 --> 00:29:41,400
- There's another boat in a half hour.
- We'll miss the parties.

445
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:43,400
We got it. Excuse me.

446
00:29:43,300 --> 00:29:45,600
- Sorry.
- Coming through.

447
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:49,100
Don't be ridiculous! What are you doing?
We are not jumping on this boat!

448
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:50,400
- Do you hear me?
- Here we go!

449
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:53,400
Listen to me, Larry, we are not
jumping on this boat!

450
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,800
- Jesus Christ! My elbow!
- Piece of cake!

451
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:59,500
Thanks, pal.

452
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:05,300
This ferry isn't leaving. It's docking.

453
00:30:06,500 --> 00:30:08,600
- Okay. We're early.
- You schmuck.

454
00:30:26,500 --> 00:30:29,100
- What is your name?
- What is your name?

455
00:30:29,100 --> 00:30:31,200
- Larry.
- Hi, Larry. I am Michelle.

456
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:34,700
Come on! Lighten up there, Rich!
We are on our way!

457
00:30:34,500 --> 00:30:38,200
I am so depressed.
I made a fool out of myself last night.

458
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:39,300
Of course you did.

459
00:30:39,300 --> 00:30:41,800
- I should've stayed home.
- What are you talking about?

460
00:30:41,700 --> 00:30:45,300
We've been summoned to the mountain top.
This is good for your career.

461
00:30:45,300 --> 00:30:49,200
You know, by the time this weekend is over,
I promise you won't even remember...

462
00:30:49,100 --> 00:30:52,100
what's- her-name's name.
I'll get you a drink. Come on.

463
00:30:52,100 --> 00:30:54,200
Look, I'll see you later.

464
00:30:54,200 --> 00:30:56,700
Goodbye, young man. Nice talking to you.

465
00:31:09,300 --> 00:31:11,600
That is good. This is very good.

466
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:19,800
- I did not hear you come in.
- I know.

467
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:22,000
I am real good at that.

468
00:31:21,900 --> 00:31:24,500
- I told you the guys aren't here yet, didn't I?
- You did.

469
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:26,300
- Good.
- Quite a shack you have here.

470
00:31:26,200 --> 00:31:27,700
It's home.

471
00:31:28,900 --> 00:31:30,500
Can I have a cigarette?

472
00:31:32,200 --> 00:31:33,300
Cigarette.

473
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:36,500
Sure.

474
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:42,600
What was...

475
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:53,800
Quite a ride, huh, Bern?

476
00:32:16,600 --> 00:32:18,800
Glorious day out, or what?

477
00:32:18,800 --> 00:32:20,200
Where's Bernie?

478
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:24,500
I got it right here. It says it's the last house
on the point, top of the dune.

479
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:28,900
Pardon me, Monsignor, sir, could you
tell me where the top of the dune is?

480
00:32:28,800 --> 00:32:32,300
- Bless you, my son.
- Thank you, Father.

481
00:32:32,500 --> 00:32:34,700
Look, we'll find it. Okay.

482
00:32:35,300 --> 00:32:38,100
- You know, it's an island, right?
- How hard can it be?

483
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:41,300
Excuse me. Is this the way to...

484
00:32:55,800 --> 00:32:59,000
- Yo, is this Bernie Lomax's house?
- Sure is.

485
00:32:59,300 --> 00:33:00,500
Wow.

486
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:03,300
Holy shit. Look at this.

487
00:33:04,700 --> 00:33:06,200
Come on, Rich.

488
00:33:08,700 --> 00:33:10,200
Oh, beautiful.

489
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:12,500
Oh, my God. He has got a pool.

490
00:33:12,700 --> 00:33:15,700
He has got a goddamn pool at the beach.
