00:47:23,400 --> 00:47:26,500
Thank you so much. This guy is like family.

735
00:47:26,500 --> 00:47:27,900
You are beautiful!

736
00:47:28,400 --> 00:47:30,900
Grab him. Larry.

737
00:47:32,800 --> 00:47:34,900
- Jesus.
- Oh, God.

738
00:47:35,500 --> 00:47:39,000
- Hi, boys. Great view.
- Hello, there. How are you?

739
00:47:41,700 --> 00:47:43,400
I give it an 8.3.

740
00:47:45,000 --> 00:47:47,400
We can't just leave him there, you know.

741
00:47:56,800 --> 00:48:01,200
<i>Girl. Beach. Sand. Surf. Moonlight.
Did you ever see Here to Eternity?</i>

742
00:48:06,500 --> 00:48:08,600
You are right. We better get him.

743
00:48:09,200 --> 00:48:12,500
- Thirty minutes. Then we call the cops.
- Not a second more.

744
00:48:16,000 --> 00:48:17,100
Ladies, how are you?

745
00:48:27,400 --> 00:48:27,900
Hi.

746
00:48:27,900 --> 00:48:28,400
Hi.

747
00:48:37,300 --> 00:48:39,500
Are we allowed to talk or anything?

748
00:48:45,200 --> 00:48:47,500
Why did you leave the party?

749
00:48:47,400 --> 00:48:50,700
I just don't feel comfortable
with most of those people.

750
00:48:50,700 --> 00:48:55,500
I don't really know any of those people.
I just know, knew, know Bernie.

751
00:48:55,900 --> 00:48:58,700
Besides, I figure
I can thank Bernie tomorrow.

752
00:48:58,700 --> 00:49:00,400
When there's more privacy.

753
00:49:01,700 --> 00:49:05,100
- Where are we going?
- There's a beautiful view from up there.

754
00:49:05,900 --> 00:49:06,900
Great.

755
00:49:14,700 --> 00:49:16,900
Ever been in a lighthouse before?

756
00:49:16,900 --> 00:49:19,800
No, this is my first time. This is great.

757
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:24,200
Does anybody live up there?
A lighthouse keeper or someone?

758
00:49:24,100 --> 00:49:26,700
No, It's all automated now. Come on.

759
00:49:29,300 --> 00:49:32,200
That takes some of the romance out of it.

760
00:49:33,700 --> 00:49:34,800
Does it?

761
00:49:53,800 --> 00:49:55,400
- You all right?
- Yeah.

762
00:50:01,000 --> 00:50:03,400
You're right. This is beautiful.

763
00:50:04,800 --> 00:50:07,800
My God.
You can see the whole island from up here.

764
00:50:11,900 --> 00:50:13,900
I've always wondered
how these things work.

765
00:50:13,900 --> 00:50:15,300
Richard, don't.

766
00:50:16,000 --> 00:50:18,400
- I can't see.
- Watch out for the trap...

767
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:21,000
door.

768
00:50:26,200 --> 00:50:27,500
Oh, my God.

769
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:36,700
- That one works.
- Richard.

770
00:50:37,800 --> 00:50:39,500
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

771
00:50:39,500 --> 00:50:41,600
- Are you sure?
- I fell down a couple of stairs.

772
00:50:41,700 --> 00:50:43,500
- Anything broken?
- Nothing's broken.

773
00:50:43,500 --> 00:50:46,300
- Are you sure?
- A little pain, but I'm all right.

774
00:50:46,200 --> 00:50:48,300
- I'm fine. How are you?
- I'm good.

775
00:50:48,600 --> 00:50:50,100
Here. Hold on.

776
00:50:50,100 --> 00:50:52,200
The good news is, I can see again.

777
00:50:58,700 --> 00:51:01,300
- I'm so sorry, Richard.
- No, it's okay, really.

778
00:51:01,300 --> 00:51:03,100
I've always wanted a limp.

779
00:51:03,700 --> 00:51:05,700
I must thank you.
This has been a great date.

780
00:51:05,700 --> 00:51:07,800
I hope my major medical covers it.

781
00:51:08,300 --> 00:51:09,300
What?

782
00:51:10,100 --> 00:51:13,700
I'm sorry. I don't mean to laugh...

783
00:51:14,100 --> 00:51:17,700
but the look on your face
when you fell through the trapdoor.

784
00:51:17,700 --> 00:51:19,700
I think I've got a cracked rib.

785
00:51:19,700 --> 00:51:22,500
- Do you want to sit down?
- No.

786
00:51:22,500 --> 00:51:26,300
No, I better not. The way things are going,
I'm gonna break my ass.

787
00:51:26,500 --> 00:51:28,100
You'll be okay.

788
00:51:55,100 --> 00:51:58,000
I've had a crush on you
since the first day I saw you at work.

789
00:51:58,000 --> 00:51:59,500
I'm crazy about you.

790
00:52:02,700 --> 00:52:04,100
This is so right.

791
00:52:06,100 --> 00:52:09,300
Oh, my God. This can't be happening to me.

792
00:52:09,200 --> 00:52:12,900
It's happening to both of us.
You're right. It's so right.

793
00:52:12,900 --> 00:52:15,600
No. This isn't right, it's all wrong.
Not here in the sand.

794
00:52:15,500 --> 00:52:16,900
- What?
- You deserve more than this.

795
00:52:17,000 --> 00:52:19,700
You need music, flowers, candles.
You need...

796
00:52:24,000 --> 00:52:26,000
You need to get out of here.

797
00:52:26,000 --> 00:52:28,900
- Are you kidding me?
- No, I'm serious. You could catch a cold.

798
00:52:28,900 --> 00:52:30,900
- Where do you live?
- Dune Walk.

799
00:52:48,200 --> 00:52:49,600
Are you dead, too?

800
00:52:50,700 --> 00:52:52,500
Mister? Hello?

801
00:52:52,900 --> 00:52:55,200
Oh, Jesus. What is it with this place?

802
00:52:57,800 --> 00:53:00,100
How are you? Party's over.
You have to go home now.

803
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:01,800
- Where's Bernie?
- He's swimming.

804
00:53:01,800 --> 00:53:04,500
I had a wonderful time.
I'm sorry I had to leave so early.

805
00:53:04,500 --> 00:53:07,000
Have fun. See you at the next one. Larry!

806
00:53:16,400 --> 00:53:18,100
Larry, are you in there?

807
00:53:18,200 --> 00:53:21,100
- Come on out, Lar. Right now.
- Go away.

808
00:53:21,000 --> 00:53:22,600
I need to talk to you.

809
00:53:24,900 --> 00:53:26,900
Can you just give me 30 seconds?

810
00:53:27,800 --> 00:53:30,000
Bernie is waiting for us.

811
00:53:31,700 --> 00:53:35,400
- Look, Bernie isn't going anywhere, okay?
- I need you, Lar.

812
00:53:35,500 --> 00:53:36,700
Bernie, he needs you, too.

813
00:53:36,800 --> 00:53:37,800
Unbelievable.

814
00:53:38,800 --> 00:53:42,100
How am I supposed to know
that the tide is gonna come up that high?

815
00:53:42,000 --> 00:53:43,900
I don't want to talk about it.

816
00:53:44,000 --> 00:53:46,500
I don't understand why this is becoming
all my fault.

817
00:53:47,400 --> 00:53:50,100
- Did you invite somebody over?
- Of course not.

818
00:53:50,000 --> 00:53:51,100
Somebody's here.

819
00:53:51,200 --> 00:53:54,000
Let's just shove him in the bedroom,
we'll say he's sleeping.

820
00:53:54,300 --> 00:53:56,900
Bernie, you cheat.

821
00:53:57,100 --> 00:53:58,300
Two-timer.

822
00:54:05,400 --> 00:54:06,800
Bernie, open up.

823
00:54:09,700 --> 00:54:11,300
Darn you, Bernie.

824
00:54:11,900 --> 00:54:13,400
Don't do this to me.

825
00:54:18,100 --> 00:54:20,800
Where the hell are you, you son of a bitch?

826
00:54:20,800 --> 00:54:23,500
I got you now, you two-timing bastard.

827
00:54:25,800 --> 00:54:28,700
Who the hell are you? Where's Bernie?

828
00:54:29,000 --> 00:54:31,100
We're Bernie's houseguests. Who are you?

829
00:54:31,200 --> 00:54:32,500
I'm his woman.

830
00:54:33,400 --> 00:54:36,900
And I'll kill him if he's cheating on me.
Now, where the hell is he?

831
00:54:36,800 --> 00:54:39,300
And don't try to cover up for him, either.

832
00:54:39,700 --> 00:54:42,000
- He's not here.
- Haven't seen him.

833
00:54:42,000 --> 00:54:43,600
I don't believe you.

834
00:54:44,700 --> 00:54:46,900
I'm gonna tear this place apart.

835
00:54:52,800 --> 00:54:55,200
- That's his woman?
- I guess so.

836
00:55:05,800 --> 00:55:07,600
Where the hell is he?

837
00:55:07,600 --> 00:55:10,200
- He's in the bedroom.
- Is that so?

838
00:55:11,600 --> 00:55:13,000
He better be alone.

839
00:55:17,600 --> 00:55:18,900
God damn it.

840
00:55:18,900 --> 00:55:20,400
Fun while it lasted, huh?

841
00:55:20,400 --> 00:55:23,600
What difference does it make,
we might as well get this over with.

842
00:55:23,600 --> 00:55:26,800
This is good. She discovers the body,
she calls the police.

843
00:55:26,700 --> 00:55:28,700
Fix me a drink, will you?

844
00:55:29,200 --> 00:55:31,100
I hate it when they scream.

845
00:55:54,900 --> 00:55:56,300
Oh, no!

846
00:56:10,700 --> 00:56:14,800
What gives? She has been up there, what,

847
00:56:15,500 --> 00:56:17,100
I don't get it.

848
00:56:46,400 --> 00:56:48,100
Got a little scotch?

849
00:56:50,000 --> 00:56:51,100
Sure.

850
00:57:02,900 --> 00:57:06,600
- Did everything go okay up there?
- Never been better.

851
00:57:11,400 --> 00:57:12,500
Good.

852
00:57:22,500 --> 00:57:26,500
How do you like that?
The guy gets laid more dead than I do alive.

853
00:57:27,400 --> 00:57:28,900
No, she couldn't have.

854
00:57:30,200 --> 00:57:31,600
He couldn't have.

855
00:57:32,200 --> 00:57:34,500
I get yelled at when I just lay there.

856
00:57:57,900 --> 00:58:02,400
Vito, I'm telling you, Lomax is alive.
She was with him for at least half an hour...

857
00:58:02,600 --> 00:58:05,900
<i>- in the bedroom.
- What were they doing in the bedroom?</i>

858
00:58:05,900 --> 00:58:07,900
I'd rather not say.

859
00:58:07,800 --> 00:58:09,900
<i>What the hell happened to Paulie?</i>

860
00:58:09,900 --> 00:58:13,400
Yeah, maybe Paulie
is rustier than we thought, huh?

861
00:58:15,600 --> 00:58:19,400
- What a night.
- Great, isn't it? It isn't over yet.

862
00:58:19,400 --> 00:58:22,500
It is for me. I'm dead. No offense, Bernie.

863
00:58:23,100 --> 00:58:25,000
I just gotta lie down for a minute.

864
00:58:25,000 --> 00:58:28,800
Suit yourself. Whatever you like.
I'm going on to find the next party.

865
00:58:29,100 --> 00:58:32,400
- Just wake me up when you get back.
- Okay, sure.

866
00:58:32,300 --> 00:58:34,800
- Whatever you like.
- Because I got to call the cops.

867
00:58:34,600 --> 00:58:37,800
- Of course you do. In the morning.
- I need a clear head.

868
00:58:38,100 --> 00:58:39,500
Good night, buddy.

869
00:58:40,000 --> 00:58:42,700
Don't forget. Wake me up.

870
00:58:51,800 --> 00:58:54,900
I made these a little sweeter this time.
Okay, Bernie?

871
00:58:55,600 --> 00:58:57,400
God, it's glorious out, huh?

872
00:58:58,800 --> 00:59:00,400
Here we go, my friend.

873
00:59:01,600 --> 00:59:03,000
This should do it.

874
00:59:05,100 --> 00:59:06,000
Okay.

875
00:59:06,400 --> 00:59:08,200
How did you deal with?

876
00:59:09,200 --> 00:59:12,100
Oriental? I think I own that one.

877
00:59:12,800 --> 00:59:14,100
With hotel.

878
00:59:15,400 --> 00:59:17,000
$550.

879
00:59:17,000 --> 00:59:19,200
Give me $600, we'll call it square.

880
00:59:19,100 --> 00:59:20,800
Hey, Bernie, Larry.

881
00:59:20,900 --> 00:59:23,500
Great party last night, Bernie.
Your best ever.

882
00:59:23,500 --> 00:59:25,800
Ladies. Hello. How are you today?

883
00:59:25,800 --> 00:59:26,800
- Great.
- Fine.

884
00:59:26,800 --> 00:59:30,200
- Are we doing it again today?
- Absolutely. You know we are.

885
00:59:30,200 --> 00:59:32,400
- Great. We'll see you later, guys.
- Bye-bye.

886
00:59:32,400 --> 00:59:34,600
Bye-bye, ladies. We'll see you later.

887
00:59:36,300 --> 00:59:38,000
Is this great or what?

888
00:59:39,200 --> 00:59:41,200
Okay, coming out. My turn.

889
00:59:41,400 --> 00:59:42,600
Shooter now.

890
00:59:43,100 --> 00:59:46,000
Yes! Free parking. $500 for me.

891
00:59:52,200 --> 00:59:53,300
Bastard!

892
00:59:58,800 --> 01:00:02,200
I own it. Okay, that is $24...

893
01:00:02,200 --> 01:00:05,200
I own them all. $46, my friend. Call it $50.

894
01:00:05,400 --> 01:00:07,900
Thank you. My turn. Here we go.

895
01:00:07,900 --> 01:00:09,500
Lucky seven coming out.

896
01:00:09,600 --> 01:00:10,600
Shit.

897
01:00:11,400 --> 01:00:15,600
One more you get out of jail free.
All right. Fine. Your turn. I'll roll.

898
01:00:15,500 --> 01:00:17,100
Here we go. Coming out.

899
01:00:19,000 --> 01:00:20,400
Community Chest.

900
01:00:21,800 --> 01:00:24,000
Second prize in a beauty contest.

901
01:00:24,400 --> 01:00:27,300
- What are you doing?
- Playing Monopoly. You want to play?

902
01:00:27,200 --> 01:00:29,200
- No.
- Here we go.

903
01:00:29,900 --> 01:00:31,900
- How did he get down here?
- He walked.

904
01:00:31,900 --> 01:00:33,200
- He walked?
- Say good morning.

905
01:00:34,000 --> 01:00:37,000
Oh, God. You're just a sick man, Larry.

906
01:00:37,400 --> 01:00:40,500
- What time is it?
- It's 11:30.

907
01:00:42,800 --> 01:00:45,500
You let me sleep till 11:30? I have...

908
01:00:46,600 --> 01:00:49,100
- When did you get a Rolex?
- Oh, this.

909
01:00:51,700 --> 01:00:54,400
- Good God!
- He didn't need it anymore.

910
01:00:54,800 --> 01:00:57,700
That's it. We're gonna go to jail.
They're gonna arrest us.

911
01:00:57,600 --> 01:01:01,300
- I'm calling the cops.
- I wanted to call them yesterday, my friend.

912
01:01:02,100 --> 01:01:04,200
He's very upset. Richard, look.

913
01:01:04,400 --> 01:01:08,400
Let me just say one thing here.
There's no reason to get pissy about this.

914
01:01:11,000 --> 01:01:12,100
Hello.

915
01:01:13,900 --> 01:01:15,800
- Richard?
- It's for you.

916
01:01:16,700 --> 01:01:18,500
- Gwen.
- Hi.

917
01:01:19,500 --> 01:01:21,300
What are you doing here?

918
01:01:24,200 --> 01:01:27,900
I just came by to talk to Bernie.
I didn't get a chance to last night, so...

919
01:01:27,900 --> 01:01:30,700
Oh, no. Bernie and I
are in a very big business meeting.

920
01:01:30,600 --> 01:01:31,800
- Now?
- Yes.

921
01:01:31,800 --> 01:01:34,800
Bernie has such little time,
so can you come back later?

922
01:01:34,800 --> 01:01:37,500
Wait a minute.
What happened to Mr. Romantic?

923
01:01:37,400 --> 01:01:41,400
- Candlelight? Flowers?
- I know. But Bernie is tied up right now.

924
01:01:43,600 --> 01:01:46,200
- It's a bad time.
- What is going on, Richard?

925
01:01:46,100 --> 01:01:48,500
Okay. I'll tell you.

926
01:01:48,500 --> 01:01:51,000
I probably shouldn't,
I know I shouldn't, but...

927
01:01:51,000 --> 01:01:54,000
at this point, why not? Mr. Lomax is...

928
01:02:02,100 --> 01:02:05,100
my boss. I work for him
at the insurance company.

929
01:02:07,900 --> 01:02:09,900
Bernie, you're starting to peel.

930
01:02:10,100 --> 01:02:12,200
Better get you out of the sun, huh?

931
01:02:14,200 --> 01:02:15,500
Here we go.

932
01:02:22,300 --> 01:02:24,900
We were really looking forward
to coming out here...

933
01:02:24,800 --> 01:02:26,800
when we got here, Mr. Lomax...

934
01:02:27,300 --> 01:02:28,700
Bernie was...

935
01:02:30,700 --> 01:02:31,700
dead.

936
01:02:33,900 --> 01:02:35,000
Dead.

937
01:02:35,200 --> 01:02:38,400
Like your mother and father were dead.
And your aunt is dead, too?

938
01:02:38,200 --> 01:02:39,200
Different kind of dead.

939
01:02:52,000 --> 01:02:54,400
You son of a bitch. I got you.

940
01:02:59,200 --> 01:03:02,800
Then how come I saw Bernie
with you and your friend at the party?

941
01:03:03,800 --> 01:03:05,400
Because...

942
01:03:07,700 --> 01:03:09,200
You don't believe me?

943
01:03:10,900 --> 01:03:13,400
Okay, I'm gonna prove it to you. Come on.

944
01:03:13,500 --> 01:03:14,900
This is not going to be fun.

945
01:03:27,200 --> 01:03:29,300
I know you think I'm crazy, but...

946
01:03:33,900 --> 01:03:34,900
Well?

947
01:03:36,400 --> 01:03:37,700
Where is Bernie?

948
01:03:38,100 --> 01:03:39,400
Oh, hello.

949
01:03:40,300 --> 01:03:42,500
- Where's Bernie?
- He went for more daiquiri mix.

950
01:03:42,500 --> 01:03:43,800
No, he didn't.

951
01:03:43,800 --> 01:03:46,600
Richard, I don't know what
this game is you're playing...

952
01:03:46,600 --> 01:03:48,300
but this is ridiculous.

953
01:03:48,300 --> 01:03:51,000
- I'm out of here.
- Gwen, I'm not playing any games with you.

954
01:03:51,000 --> 01:03:53,500
I'm telling you the truth! Bernie is here.

955
01:03:54,800 --> 01:03:56,500
Where is Bernie?

956
01:03:56,500 --> 01:03:59,200
What, you bastard, did you do with Bernie?

957
01:04:03,500 --> 01:04:05,200
I'm phoning the police.

958
01:04:11,200 --> 01:04:14,000
There's no dial tone. With 97 buttons...

959
01:04:15,700 --> 01:04:18,700
<i>- Where is your house?
- Where is the off button?</i>

960
01:04:18,700 --> 01:04:21,700
<i>Look, Paulie, just don't kill them
while I'm around.</i>

961
01:04:21,700 --> 01:04:24,700
<i>- Bernie, we're on a phone here.
- You're right.</i>

962
01:04:24,600 --> 01:04:27,100
- Play that back.
- I just got it stopped.

963
01:04:27,100 --> 01:04:28,700
Play it back, please.

964
01:04:31,600 --> 01:04:34,800
<i>Hey, Lomax, it's Paulie.
I just got to the island.</i>

965
01:04:35,100 --> 01:04:36,100
<i>You're early.</i>

966
01:04:36,200 --> 01:04:38,500
<i>Those two schmucks
won't come until the 6:00 ferry...</i>

967
01:04:38,500 --> 01:04:41,200
<i>- and I still have to plant the note.
- Yeah.</i>

968
01:04:41,500 --> 01:04:44,800
<i>- Where is your house?
- It's on the point, top of the dune.</i>

969
01:04:45,100 --> 01:04:46,700
<i>Look, Paulie...</i>

970
01:04:46,900 --> 01:04:50,400
<i>- don't kill them while I'm around.
- Bernie, we're on the phone here.</i>

971
01:04:50,400 --> 01:04:52,300
<i>You're right. I'm sorry.</i>

972
01:04:52,300 --> 01:04:55,300
<i>The point is, I just want to be
back in New York with an alibi.</i>

973
01:04:55,300 --> 01:04:56,800
<i>Don't worry about it.</i>

974
01:05:00,900 --> 01:05:02,800
We were on the 6:00 ferry.

975
01:05:04,500 --> 01:05:06,100
And we're two schmucks.

976
01:05:08,900 --> 01:05:11,000
- Kill us?
