01:20:15,000 --> 01:20:17,000
This is tougher than it looks.

1229
01:20:17,000 --> 01:20:18,900
You're doing very well, Richard.

1230
01:20:18,900 --> 01:20:21,000
- Sorry I snapped at you.
- It's okay.

1231
01:20:21,000 --> 01:20:23,300
I've never been chased by a killer before.

1232
01:20:23,300 --> 01:20:25,600
It's all right. You're doing very well.

1233
01:20:27,300 --> 01:20:30,400
- Why is everybody waving at us?
- I'm popular.

1234
01:20:30,300 --> 01:20:31,300
I see.

1235
01:20:31,300 --> 01:20:33,300
Hey, Bernie, showing off again?

1236
01:20:36,100 --> 01:20:38,700
Oh, God. What the hell are those things?

1237
01:20:39,500 --> 01:20:42,300
Those are obviously channel markers.

1238
01:20:42,600 --> 01:20:43,500
Obviously.

1239
01:20:43,600 --> 01:20:46,600
Okay, wise ass, do you know
what side I'm supposed to pass on?

1240
01:20:46,500 --> 01:20:49,400
That I don't know. Just stay close.
What else can happen here?

1241
01:20:49,300 --> 01:20:50,600
I've got no idea.

1242
01:20:51,200 --> 01:20:53,700
- Serpentine.
- Is that close enough?

1243
01:20:57,600 --> 01:20:59,200
Do you hear something?

1244
01:21:02,800 --> 01:21:04,500
- There it's again.
- Yeah.

1245
01:21:04,800 --> 01:21:07,100
- I wonder what that is.
- What is that?

1246
01:21:12,500 --> 01:21:14,200
- Man overboard.
- What?

1247
01:21:14,300 --> 01:21:15,600
Stop the boat.

1248
01:21:18,500 --> 01:21:20,000
He's got nice form.

1249
01:21:24,200 --> 01:21:26,200
- I don't know.
- I'm trying to drive a boat.

1250
01:21:26,300 --> 01:21:29,100
- You're doing well.
- Trying to get us off this island of hell.

1251
01:21:29,000 --> 01:21:31,100
You had maybe one job to do.
Watch a dead body.

1252
01:21:31,100 --> 01:21:33,600
- Well, let's not argue about it.
- Jesus.

1253
01:21:34,500 --> 01:21:37,500
- You were the one who tied him up.
- Don't blame this all on me.

1254
01:21:37,500 --> 01:21:39,600
- Oh, my God.
- What?

1255
01:21:39,900 --> 01:21:41,600
You've lost my sunglasses.

1256
01:21:59,600 --> 01:22:01,000
What are you doing?

1257
01:22:02,400 --> 01:22:03,900
I haven't got a clue.

1258
01:22:05,500 --> 01:22:07,000
I don't believe this.

1259
01:22:07,400 --> 01:22:08,600
What?

1260
01:22:10,500 --> 01:22:11,800
We're out of gas.

1261
01:22:14,600 --> 01:22:17,000
Paddling in the Atlantic Ocean...

1262
01:22:17,200 --> 01:22:19,800
- on a dead body.
- I'm getting swimmer's ear.

1263
01:22:19,900 --> 01:22:22,000
This is now the perfect weekend.

1264
01:22:22,100 --> 01:22:26,300
It started when I almost broke my leg
jumping on a moving ferry.

1265
01:22:26,500 --> 01:22:30,300
I get to this beautiful beach and my host...
Sorry, he's dead.

1266
01:22:34,100 --> 01:22:35,400
Hampton Island.

1267
01:22:37,000 --> 01:22:39,500
Checkers. Excuse me, sir.
Is this your launch?

1268
01:22:39,500 --> 01:22:41,700
- Come on, let's go.
- Don't rush.

1269
01:22:44,700 --> 01:22:46,100
Come on.

1270
01:22:46,100 --> 01:22:49,200
- Can you put a little snap in it, fellows?
- Okay, Cappy.

1271
01:22:54,500 --> 01:22:56,300
Hold on, you damn fool.

1272
01:22:56,400 --> 01:23:00,100
I fell down a lighthouse.
I had a corpse wash up...

1273
01:23:00,000 --> 01:23:01,300
next to me on the shore.

1274
01:23:01,400 --> 01:23:05,700
And then I find out that my dead boss
is not only a thief, he wants to kill me.

1275
01:23:11,300 --> 01:23:12,600
I almost drown.

1276
01:23:12,700 --> 01:23:15,600
The girl of my dreams
now thinks I'm a raving lunatic.

1277
01:23:15,600 --> 01:23:17,300
You mean what's- her-name?

1278
01:23:18,200 --> 01:23:20,700
And, now, we're going back
to the house of death.

1279
01:23:20,700 --> 01:23:22,900
- Great weekend, huh?
- Great weekend!

1280
01:23:25,700 --> 01:23:28,200
Just get here as fast as you can.
Thanks, Ed.

1281
01:23:28,200 --> 01:23:29,300
Police is on the way.

1282
01:23:29,400 --> 01:23:31,900
Can just lock ourselves in
until they get here?

1283
01:23:31,900 --> 01:23:34,300
I hate it when he stares at me like that.

1284
01:23:34,300 --> 01:23:35,600
Let's go.

1285
01:23:38,100 --> 01:23:39,800
Put him in his bathroom.

1286
01:23:43,000 --> 01:23:45,600
- Bernie's picked up a little weight.
- What do you expect?

1287
01:23:45,600 --> 01:23:47,600
He's been soaking in the ocean
for two hours.

1288
01:23:47,600 --> 01:23:48,900
Made a damn good float though.

1289
01:23:53,600 --> 01:23:55,000
Are you in here?

1290
01:24:08,700 --> 01:24:10,200
It's Gwen.

1291
01:24:11,600 --> 01:24:12,800
Hi, Gwen.

1292
01:24:12,800 --> 01:24:15,500
You've got to be the weirdest guy
I've ever met.

1293
01:24:16,000 --> 01:24:18,100
You told me Bernie was dead, right?

1294
01:24:18,100 --> 01:24:19,900
I just saw you with him.

1295
01:24:19,900 --> 01:24:21,900
What's your explanation this time?

1296
01:24:21,900 --> 01:24:24,400
I don't mean to be rude,
but get the hell out of here.

1297
01:24:24,400 --> 01:24:27,700
No, I'm not going anywhere
until you tell me what is going on.

1298
01:24:27,700 --> 01:24:28,700
Listen to me!

1299
01:24:28,700 --> 01:24:32,000
You're in danger here,
leave unless you want to get shot.

1300
01:24:32,800 --> 01:24:35,600
Lomax is dead,
somebody is trying to kill us.

1301
01:24:35,500 --> 01:24:38,600
Can we stay at your house
until the cops come or what?

1302
01:24:40,700 --> 01:24:42,200
It's just Bernie.

1303
01:24:45,700 --> 01:24:48,800
Gwen, listen to me.

1304
01:24:48,800 --> 01:24:51,900
We didn't do this to him.
Do we look like we could kill someone?

1305
01:24:51,900 --> 01:24:54,100
Honey, have a drink, relax. You'll be fine.

1306
01:24:54,100 --> 01:24:56,800
Let me rephrase that.
Do I look like I could kill someone?

1307
01:24:56,800 --> 01:24:58,500
What is going on in there?

1308
01:25:03,000 --> 01:25:05,800
- Which one of you bastards hit me?
- Son of a bitch.

1309
01:25:07,300 --> 01:25:09,400
You want to get your butt kicked?

1310
01:25:14,200 --> 01:25:15,500
I can explain.

1311
01:25:34,200 --> 01:25:35,400
Company.

1312
01:25:38,700 --> 01:25:41,500
I didn't see anything.
I was looking at my watch.

1313
01:25:41,900 --> 01:25:43,100
I'm blind.

1314
01:25:52,900 --> 01:25:54,100
It's empty.

1315
01:25:55,100 --> 01:25:57,400
That's right. But this ain't.

1316
01:26:01,200 --> 01:26:02,200
Run!

1317
01:26:02,400 --> 01:26:03,600
Move it! This way!

1318
01:26:06,600 --> 01:26:07,600
It's locked.

1319
01:26:07,600 --> 01:26:10,000
What are you doing?
We're friends of Bernie's.

1320
01:26:10,000 --> 01:26:11,700
I hate Bernie's friends.

1321
01:26:17,000 --> 01:26:18,000
This way.

1322
01:26:18,900 --> 01:26:20,400
To the bedroom.

1323
01:26:21,500 --> 01:26:23,600
Come on, let's go. Up.

1324
01:26:23,700 --> 01:26:26,200
You're dead meat, you little bastards.

1325
01:26:30,700 --> 01:26:32,300
Now I'm really mad!

1326
01:26:32,700 --> 01:26:34,100
Wait.

1327
01:26:34,000 --> 01:26:37,500
- What?
- You take Gwen, you go hide...

1328
01:26:37,500 --> 01:26:40,600
I'll let him chase me,
you try and call the cops, okay?

1329
01:26:40,600 --> 01:26:42,900
Okay? That's it? No arguments?

1330
01:26:43,800 --> 01:26:46,000
I'll get you all, one by one.

1331
01:26:46,000 --> 01:26:48,200
There's no place to hide.

1332
01:27:02,200 --> 01:27:03,900
I'm gonna die.

1333
01:27:21,700 --> 01:27:24,200
You kicked me, you bastard.

1334
01:27:26,300 --> 01:27:28,000
Shit! Out of bullets.

1335
01:27:57,300 --> 01:27:58,700
Sit the hell down.

1336
01:28:02,800 --> 01:28:04,200
Hang on, Lar.

1337
01:28:06,400 --> 01:28:09,000
- Coming.
- I got him.

1338
01:28:12,900 --> 01:28:14,100
Get off.

1339
01:28:14,600 --> 01:28:16,300
- Hang on, Lar.
- I got him.

1340
01:28:18,400 --> 01:28:22,100
Stand up. Fight like a man.
Come on. Put them up, you chicken.

1341
01:28:25,400 --> 01:28:26,900
Watch this, Richard.

1342
01:28:36,300 --> 01:28:37,800
All right, Lar.

1343
01:28:44,500 --> 01:28:46,200
Fists of steel.

1344
01:28:48,300 --> 01:28:50,000
Bernie, let go of me.

1345
01:28:50,700 --> 01:28:52,500
I always liked you, Bernie.

1346
01:28:56,600 --> 01:28:57,900
I got it, thanks.

1347
01:28:58,100 --> 01:29:00,600
Just a little closer. Just get the two of us.

1348
01:29:00,500 --> 01:29:02,300
Get the handshake in, okay?

1349
01:29:02,500 --> 01:29:06,400
Wait a minute. I think I blinked. Did I blink?
I think I blinked a second there.

1350
01:29:06,200 --> 01:29:08,400
- He blinked.
- He blinked. I saw him.

1351
01:29:08,400 --> 01:29:09,900
Make sure he's wrapped up good.

1352
01:29:09,900 --> 01:29:11,200
Wait a minute.

1353
01:29:13,900 --> 01:29:16,000
I didn't kill him. He's not dead.

1354
01:29:16,700 --> 01:29:18,200
I tried to kill him.

1355
01:29:19,400 --> 01:29:21,100
Look at him. He's alive.

1356
01:29:22,500 --> 01:29:24,800
- He's not dead. He's alive.
- Move it.

1357
01:29:24,700 --> 01:29:26,700
That man is alive!

1358
01:29:27,700 --> 01:29:28,800
Now what?

1359
01:29:30,100 --> 01:29:31,600
Now I'm gonna take a week off.

1360
01:29:31,600 --> 01:29:34,600
You're taking a vacation?
The man who won't take a coffee break?

1361
01:29:34,600 --> 01:29:37,100
Gwen just invited me to stay with her.
What should I say?

1362
01:29:37,100 --> 01:29:40,400
You're kidding me. You invited him?
You fool. That's fabulous.

1363
01:29:40,300 --> 01:29:42,400
You deserve it, Richard.
The company owes you.

1364
01:29:42,500 --> 01:29:44,800
Just a couple of days
until Gwen leaves for school.

1365
01:29:44,800 --> 01:29:47,500
There's plenty of room
if you want to stay, Lar.

1366
01:29:48,700 --> 01:29:52,100
Me? Oh, no, thanks.
I'll just tough it out here at Bernie's.

1367
01:29:52,000 --> 01:29:55,100
I hear the party Saturday night is
better than Friday, actually.

1368
01:30:00,100 --> 01:30:01,400
What is going on?

1369
01:30:02,000 --> 01:30:05,100
- What's happened?
- Didn't you hear? Bernie Lomax got killed.

1370
01:30:05,100 --> 01:30:06,400
- No.
- Yeah.

1371
01:30:06,400 --> 01:30:08,900
- Did you go to that party last night?
- No.

1372
01:30:09,000 --> 01:30:12,700
Lawrence, you done real good.
I'm proud of you.

1373
01:30:13,500 --> 01:30:16,500
Yeah, I did okay, huh? Surprised myself.

1374
01:30:17,500 --> 01:30:19,000
You did great, Rich.

1375
01:30:26,900 --> 01:30:29,900
Hi, Bernie. See you at the party tonight.

1376
01:30:30,200 --> 01:30:31,400
What?

1377
01:30:33,200 --> 01:30:35,400
What did she say?

1378
01:30:41,800 --> 01:30:44,000
Mister, can I bury you?

1379
01:30:45,900 --> 01:30:46,900
Great!

